5000|$|Changüí {{is related}} to the other {{regional}} genres of nengón and kiribá and is descended from nengón. Technically, the changüi ensemble consists of: marímbula, bongos, tres, güiro (or guayo) and one or more singers. Changüi does not use the Cuban key pattern (or guide pattern) known <b>as</b> <b>clave.</b> The tres typically plays offbeat guajeos (ostinatos), while the guayo plays on the beat.|$|R
