50|$|Bell pattern 1 is {{the most}} basic, or archetypal pattern. It is the 4/4 form {{of what is known}} in ethnomusicology as the {{standard}} pattern, and known in Cuba <b>as</b> <b>clave.</b> Pattern 1 is used in maculelê and some Candomblé and Macumba rhythms. Bell 2 is used in afoxê and {{can be thought of as}} pattern 1 embellished with four additional strokes. Bell 3 is used in batucada. Pattern 4 is the maracatu bell and can be thought of as pattern 1 embellished with four additional strokes.|$|R
